AMENDMENT OF THE SUPREME COURT JUDGES (SALARIES AND CONDITIONS OF SERVICE) ACT, 1958
CHAPTER III
AMENDMENT OF THE SUPREME COURT JUDGES (SALARIES AND CONDITIONS OF SERVICE) ACT, 1958
749320 6Amendment of section 13.- In section 13 of the Supreme Court Judges (Salaries and Conditions of Service) Act, 1958 (hereinafter referred to as the Supreme Court Judges Act), clause (a) shall be omitted.
1861987 7Insertion of new section 13A.- After section 13 of the Supreme Court Judges Act, the following section shall be inserted, namely:- " 13A. Benefit of added years of service.- Subject to the provisions of this Act, a period of ten years shall be added to the service of a Judge for the purposes of his pension, who qualified for appointment as such judge under sub- clause (b) of clause (3) of article 124 of the Constitution.".
1576353 8 Amendment of section 16A.- In the Supreme Court Judges Act, in section 16A, in sub- section 1,-
